## Gate 5 — Staging Deploy & Smoke Test

Deploy to staging and run a structured smoke test before touching production.

1. Trigger a staging deployment via the CI/CD pipeline (merge to main or manual trigger).
2. Wait for the deployment to complete and the health check to return 200.
3. Run the following smoke tests against the staging URL:

```
Smoke test checklist — staging:
[ ] GET /api/health returns 200 { status: "ok" }
[ ] Frontend loads at staging URL (no blank screen, no console errors)
[ ] Auth flow works end-to-end (register → login → access protected route → logout)
[ ] Core user task 1 completes successfully (from UX spec)
[ ] Core user task 2 completes successfully
[ ] Database migration applied (check schema version endpoint or migration log)
[ ] No 500 errors in staging logs during smoke test
[ ] Email/SMS (if applicable) sends and is received in test account
```

If any smoke test fails: stop, file a bug, send it back to the relevant engineer (FE or BE), and re-run the smoke test after the fix is deployed to staging.

**Output block:**
```
GATE 5 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Staging URL: [url]
Smoke tests passed: [count / total]
Smoke test failures: [list — must be 0 to proceed]
```

