## Gate 6 — Production Deploy

Deploy to production only after staging smoke tests pass and manual approval is given.

1. Trigger the production deployment (merge to release branch or approve the GitHub Environment gate).
2. Confirm production deployment steps run in order:
   - Run database migrations (pre-deploy hook)
   - Deploy new application version
   - Run health check — confirm `/api/health` returns 200
   - Confirm old version traffic drains (if blue/green or canary)
3. Run a production smoke test (subset of staging smoke test — auth + core task 1 only, using a test account, not real user data).
4. Monitor error rate for 10 minutes post-deploy. If error rate spikes above baseline, trigger rollback.

**Rollback procedure** (document in runbook):
```bash
# Rollback to previous deployment
[platform rollback command, e.g.]
fly deploy --image [previous-image-tag]
# or
vercel rollback [deployment-id]
# or
git revert [commit] && git push origin main
```

**Output block:**
```
GATE 6 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Production URL: [url]
Deploy method: [blue-green / rolling / atomic]
Rollback command documented: yes / no
Post-deploy error spike: none / [description]
```

