## Gate 7 — Monitoring & Alerting

Set up observability before declaring the deployment done.

**Error tracking:**
- Integrate Sentry (or equivalent): `npm install @sentry/node @sentry/browser`
- Capture all unhandled exceptions and promise rejections
- Set up a Sentry project for both frontend and backend
- Configure `SENTRY_DSN` as an environment variable (never hardcoded)
- Set alert threshold: notify on > 5 new errors in 5 minutes

**Uptime monitoring:**
- Set up an uptime check on `/api/health` using: Betterstack / UptimeRobot / AWS CloudWatch / Datadog
- Check interval: every 1 minute
- Alert on: 2 consecutive failures → page/email the on-call contact

**Performance baseline:**
- Record initial response times for key endpoints (P50, P95) in the runbook
- Set a performance alert if P95 latency exceeds 2× the baseline for 5 minutes

**Logging:**
- Confirm structured JSON logging is in place (not plain text)
- Logs include: timestamp, level, request_id, user_id (if authenticated), message
- Logs are shipped to a log aggregator (Logtail / Datadog / CloudWatch / Papertrail)
- Log retention: minimum 30 days

**Output block:**
```
GATE 7 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Error tracking: [Sentry / other / none]
Uptime monitoring: [tool + check URL]
Log aggregator: [tool]
```

